sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64038
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a variant of the pCASP secretion circuit with the invB chaperone and sopE2 secretion signal
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The source parts for this device come from Salmonella LT2 Genomic DNA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with biobrick standard assembly compatibility in mind, it might contain scar sequence cutsites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64016
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the 105 amino acid secretion signal for the sopE2 effector protein in Salmonella Type III Secretion. The sequence includes components necessary for directing a fused protein to the export apparatus and secretion to the extracellular space. The cognate chaperone for this sequence is invB (BBa_J64009) and is required to be co-expressed for high titer secretion of protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with compliance to biobrick standard assembly in mind.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The InvB protein is a promiscuous chaperone in the Type III Secretion system (T3S) that assists in the secretion of SipA, SopA, and SopE2 effector proteins. This chaperone binds to the secretion signal of selected proteins and maintains the N-terminus in an unfolded state for secretion by the T3S. The chaperone is critical in coordinating the timing and localization to the proper secretion mechanism and is vital in secreting heterologous proteins with this system.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed to be compatible with biobricks standard assembly

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The natural RBS that drives invB
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The expression level of this RBS has not been quantified.
